## PART 4 — The Live Demo *(60 seconds)*

> [!TIP]
> Switch to the browser now. Have `http://localhost:8000` open.

**SPEAKER 1:**

"Let me show you NEXUS running live right now.

*(Point to the Risk Gauge)*
This is our Model Risk Index. Right now it is at [READ THE NUMBER]. This tells us we are currently in a [read the regime: normal, elevated, or critical instability] regime. Below it, you can see risk momentum — how fast model risk is changing over the last hour and twenty-four hours.

*(Point to the Risk History Chart)*
Here is the full twenty-four-hour history. You can see exactly when narrative pressure spiked and when it cooled off.

*(Point to the Narrative Table)*
These are the active narrative directions NEXUS has discovered from live news. Every single name here — [read one or two names out loud] — was generated automatically by our **Qwen 2.5 model running on Modal**. No human labeled any of these.

*(Click a high-risk narrative to open the detail modal)*
If I click into this one, I get the full breakdown — surprise and impact time series, the contributing headlines, and the overall risk trajectory.

*(Type a ticker like NVDA or JPM in the search bar)*
And here is something powerful. I can search any stock ticker and NEXUS uses our **Modal-deployed embedding model** to compute the semantic similarity between that company and all active narratives. It shows me the results in a **three-dimensional vector space visualization** so I can see exactly which narratives are closest to a given stock. That three-D view is built with Three.js and the proximity distances come directly from the same embeddings that our Modal Embedder produces.

All of this is happening live. The pipeline just scraped real news, sent it through our Modal GPU for embedding, routed it through ChromaDB, scored it, and pushed updates to this dashboard in real time."

---

## PART 5 — Why Modal Specifically *(30 seconds)*

**SPEAKER 2:**

"A quick note on why we chose Modal specifically. We needed GPU inference for embeddings and LLM inference for narrative labeling, but we did not want to manage any infrastructure. Modal lets us define our models as Python classes with decorators, deploy them with one command — `modal deploy` — and call them remotely from our FastAPI backend like they are local functions. Modal handles the container image builds, the GPU provisioning, and the auto-scaling. Our containers idle-timeout after five minutes so we are not paying for GPU time when nothing is happening. The entire deployment — two model classes, two container images, one app — deploys in under two minutes."

---

## PART 6 — Impact and What Is Next *(30 seconds)*

**SPEAKER 1:**

"NEXUS addresses a problem that costs the financial industry billions of dollars during every crisis. Today, risk management is reactive — people read the news and make judgment calls. NEXUS makes it quantitative and continuous.

We built this as a working, end-to-end system — not a slide deck. Real data flowing in from ninety-plus sources. Real AI models running on Modal GPUs. Real risk scores updating every two minutes. Running right now, live, on this laptop.

If we had more time, we would add alert thresholds that auto-notify traders when model risk spikes, backtesting against historical crises like March 2020, and direct integration with trading platforms.

Thank you. We are happy to take questions."

